  "description": {
    "en": "Coyotes are highly vocal and adaptable canines that can thrive in deserts, forests, and even cities.",
    "zh": "郊狼是发声频繁且适应性极强的犬科动物，能在沙漠、森林甚至城市中繁衍。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Coyotes are medium-sized canines that look like a smaller, thinner version of a wolf. They weigh between 7 and 20 kilograms and have pointed ears, a narrow snout, and a bushy tail with a black tip. Their fur is usually grayish-brown on top and lighter on the belly, helping them blend into their surroundings.",
      "zh": "郊狼是中等体型的犬科动物，看起来像是狼的缩小版，更加纤细。它们体重在7到20公斤之间，有尖尖的耳朵、细长的鼻子和一条末端为黑色的蓬松尾巴。它们的毛通常上面是灰棕色、腹部较浅，有助于融入周围环境。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Coyotes are omnivores that eat rabbits, rodents, fruit, insects, and sometimes garbage from humans. They are famous for their haunting howls, which they use to communicate with family members across long distances. Coyotes often hunt alone or in pairs, but may form small packs in winter when larger prey is available.",
      "zh": "郊狼是杂食动物，吃兔子、啮齿类动物、水果、昆虫，有时还吃人类的垃圾。它们最出名的是那令人难忘的嚎叫声，用来和远方的家人沟通。郊狼通常单独或成对狩猎，但在冬天有较大猎物时，可能会组成小群体。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Coyotes originally lived in the prairies and deserts of western North America, but have now spread to almost every corner of the continent, including big cities like Los Angeles and Chicago. They are one of the most adaptable animals in the world. They can live in deserts, grasslands, forests, mountains, and urban neighborhoods.",
      "zh": "郊狼最初生活在北美洲西部的草原和沙漠中，但如今已经扩展到了大陆的几乎每一个角落，包括洛杉矶和芝加哥等大城市。它们是世界上适应性最强的动物之一，能生活在沙漠、草原、森林、山脉和城市社区中。"
    }
  },
